catalogue.definition:
This Data Item allows for a more convenient handling of the messages
at the receiver side by further defining the type of transaction.

catalogue.definition: Last valid and credible flight level used to update the track, in two's complement representation.
catalogue.remark:
Note:
     The criteria to determine the credibility of the flight level are Tracker dependent.
     Credible means: within reasonable range of change with respect to the previous detection.
catalogue.title: Measured Flight Level

catalogue.definition: Calculated Track Geometric Altitude Calculated geometric vertical distance above mean sea level, not related to barometric pressure.
catalogue.remark:
Note:
     The source of altitude is identified in bits (SRC) of item I011/170 Track Status.
catalogue.title: Calculated Track Geometric Altitude

catalogue.definition: Calculated Barometric Altitude of the track.

catalogue.definition: Absolute time stamping expressed as UTC.

catalogue.definition: Target (aircraft or vehicle) identification in 8 characters.

Note:
    Characters 1-8 (coded on 6 bits each) defining target identification

values: Callsign or registration downlinked from transponde

catalogue.definition: Target size defined as length and with of the detected target, and orientation.
catalogue.remark:
Note:
    The orientation gives the direction which the aircraft nose is pointing, relative to the Geographical North.
catalogue.title: Target Size and Orientation

catalogue.definition: Ages of the last plot/local track, or the last valid mode-A/mode-C, used to update the system track.
catalogue.remark:
Note:
    The ages are counted from Data Item I011/140, Time Of Track
    Information, using the following formula:
    Age = Time of track information - Time of last (valid) update
    If the computed age is greater than the maximum value or if the
    data has never been received, then the corresponding subfield is not sent.
catalogue.title: System Track Update Ages
